  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to fill in 'Name' first and then 'Password' when I'm creating a new account, so that I can follow a more logical onboarding flow.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n*Summary*: As part of [testing the onboarding flow with users](https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1eJP-Hh4tN6XZREIy73GNuJP1LqGg41EvP5QpVlFZQ78/edit#slide=id.g3e1b33ca7e_2_121), we found that asking first for a Password and then for a Name can create some confusion among users and increases their cognitive load (they have to think twice).\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nExpected order of screens:\r\n\r\n1- Initial screen\r\n**2- Name screen**\r\n**3- Password screen**\r\n**4- Confirm password screen**\r\n5- Welcome screen\r\n\r\n![onboarding min - mobile](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/43401758-60931ffa-93e7-11e8-9e4a-785f345f34e6.png)\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nCurrent order of screens:\r\n\r\n1- Initial screen\r\n**2- Password screen**\r\n**3- Confirm password screen**\r\n**4- Name screen**\r\n5- Welcome screen\r\n\r\n![onboarding min - mobile copy](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/43400665-b14ccbce-93e4-11e8-9b1f-c1bba42f0fc8.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Select \"Other accounts\"\r\n- Select \"Create new account\"\r\n- Follow account creating steps\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n Switch the order of the 'name' & 'password' steps during account creation. **Make sure that both **\"Next\"** and **\"Back\"** buttons follow the new sequence of steps.**\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n- To be implemented on Android & iOS.\r\n- @obi2020 should create copy changes on \"Create account\" label in the \"Confirm account\" step once this issue gets implemented (not before). \r\n- Other onboarding issues related are: \"Creating your account on the blockchain...\" screen removal here #5337 .",
